| last=Fagan| title=Loud music leads to teen's shooting in Antioch|date=2009-09-17|work=San Francisco Chronicle|url = http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2009/09/16/BA4B19O1ER.DTL|accessdate = 2009-09-17}}</ref> The victim was [[air ambulance|lifted by air]] to [[John Muir Medical Center]] in [[Walnut Creek, California|Walnut Creek]] and underwent surgery. Yousuf Mohammad Aziz, a 19-year-old graduate of Deer Valley, was arrested on September 18 in connection with the shooting.<ref name=\"contracosta919\">{{cite news|first=Hilary| last=Costa| title=\nAntioch school officials stand by emergency protocol|date=2009-09-19|publisher= [[Contra Costa Times]]|url =\nhttp://www.contracostatimes.com/education/ci_13377161|accessdate = 2009-09-19}}</ref> Aziz was found guilty of attempted murder, and was sentenced to 7 years to life in prison. \n|-\n| September 17, 2009\n| [[Ansbach]],<br>[[Bavaria]],<br>Germany\n| Georg R., 18\n|\n| 11 injured\n| [[Ansbach school attack]]. An 18-year-old student identified as Georg R. arrived at Carolinum High School in [[Ansbach]], Germany armed with an [[axe]], knives and [[Molotov cocktails]]. He injured nine students and a teacher at the school before he himself was shot by police. Two of the injured students as well as the attacker were reported to be in critical condition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/teenage-attacker-wounds-school-students-germany/story?id=8599482 |title=Teenage Attacker Wounds 9 School Students in Germany |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |date=2009-09-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 23, 2009\n| [[Tyler, Texas|Tyler]],<br>[[Texas]],<br>United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 50-year-old Todd Henry, a [[special education]] teacher at [[John Tyler High School]], was fatally stabbed by a student inside a classroom at the school. Henry later died of his injuries at a local hospital. The attacker was taken into custody.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abcnews.go.com/US/texas-teacher-s