hool, was shot to death by students Billy Ray Powell, 16, and Hugh Justice, 19.  The assailants had been reprimanded by Sweatt, and accosted him outside his office.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://digital.olivesoftware.com/Repository/TWH/1951/03/13/035-TWH-1951-03-13-001-SINGLE.pdf#OLV0_Entity_0001_0007|work=The Winona Republican-Herald|title=2 Youths Held in Slaying of Teacher, Chum|page=1|date=Mar 13, 1951|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202082124/http://digital.olivesoftware.com/Repository/TWH/1951/03/13/035-TWH-1951-03-13-001-SINGLE.pdf#OLV0_Entity_0001_0007|archivedate=2016-02-02}}</ref>\n|-\n| June 4, 1951\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| \n| 1 dead\n|\n| Carl Arch, a 50-year-old intruder to a girls' gym class, was shot and killed by a police officer at Manhattan's Central Commercial High School.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1951/06/05/archives/policemans-shot-kills-crazed-man-who-invades-46th-st-girls-school.html|work=The New York Times|title=Crazed Man Killed in Girls' School|date=Jun 5, 1951}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 27, 1951\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| David Brooks, a 15-year-old student, was fatally shot by two former students, as fellow pupils looked on in a grade school.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1951/11/27/archives/st-louis-pupil-killed-two-former-students-sought-in-grade-school.html?sq=%2522a+15+year+old+student%2522&scp=2&st=p|work=The New York Times|title=St. Louis Pupil Killed|date=Nov 27, 1951}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 9, 1952\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| ..., 15\n| \n| 1 injured\n| A 15-year-old boarding school student shot a dean rather than relinquish pin-up pictures of girls in bathing suits.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1952/04/09/archives/dean-shot-over-pinups-georgia-student-15-refused-to-give-up.html?sq=%2522a+15+year+old%2522&scp=2&st=p|work=The New York Times|title=Dean Shot Over Pin Ups|date=Apr 9, 195