piegel.de/panorama/justiz/0,1518,449549,00.html|title = Massenmorde in der Schule|publisher= www.spiegel.de }}</ref>\n|-\n| April 20, 2000\n| [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| ..., 15\n|\n| 5 injured\n| A 15-year-old student at [[Cairine Wilson Secondary School]] in the suburban community of [[Orleans, Ontario|Orleans]] pulled out a knife and stabbed a fellow student whom he was conversing with, and then ran through the school stabbing another three students and a teacher's aide. Michael Jordan, the school principal finally convinced the youth to surrender the weapon.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2000/04/22/stabbingcharges000422.html |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120722075250/http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2000/04/22/stabbingcharges000422.html |archive-date=2012-07-22 |title=Boy charged with Ontario school stabbing |publisher=Cbc.ca |date=2000-11-11 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 26, 2000\n| [[Lake Worth, Florida]], United States\n| [[Nathaniel Brazill]], 13\n| 1 dead\n|\n| One teacher, Barry Grunow, had been shot and killed at Lake Worth Middle School by 13-year-old Nate Brazill with .25-caliber semiautomatic pistol on the last day of classes. Brazill was convicted of the murder and sentenced to twenty-five years in prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/story?id=93260&page=1|title=Brazill Guilty of Second-Degree Murder|first=A. B. C.|last=News|date=7 January 2006|website=ABC News}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 26, 2000\n| [[New Orleans, Louisiana]], United States\n| \n| \n| 2 injured\n| Darrel Johnson, 13, and Alfred Anderson were initially charged with [[Louisiana]] attempted second degree murder in a school shooting where both were shot with the same gun.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Jury Is Still Out|url=http://www.bestofneworleans.com/gambit/the-jury-is-still-out/Content?oid=1239849|date=January 8, 2002}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 19, 2000\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Rickley Gregoire, 16<br>Eduardo Hall, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 12-year-old Anthony Haynes is stabbed to death in the cafeteria of [[Canarsie High School]]. Two 16-year-old students were arrested for the crime. It was suspected that the stabbing was gang-related.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gootman |first=Elissa |url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F70C15FC3B5A0C738EDDA90994D8404482 |title=Boy Is Stabbed in Brooklyn After School-Cafeteria Fight |location=New York City |publisher=Select.nytimes.com |date=2000-10-20 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 23, 2000\n| [[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 20-year-old security guard Reginald Millsaps is shot to death at Western Academy Community Education Center by an unknown assailant.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/62881135.html?dids=62881135:62881135&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+24%2C+2000&author=&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&desc=SOUTHERN+CALIFORNIA+%2F+A+news+summary%3B+Security+Guard+Dead+After+Shooting+at+South-Central+School&pqatl=google |title=Security Guard Dead After Shooting at South-Central School |publisher=Pqasb.pqarchiver.com |date=2000-10-24 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 24, 2000\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| While changing a tire on a teacher\u2019s car outside Bushwick High School, 18-year-old Joseph Gallo Rodriguez was accosted by two men looking to rob him of a silver crucifix. When he refused the robbers shot him and fled. Rodriguez died of the gunshot wound the next day.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gootman |first=Elissa |url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F20D12FF3B550C758EDDA90994D8404482 |title=18-Year-Old Is Fatally Shot While Helping Change Tire |location=New York City |publisher=Select.nytimes.com |date=2000-10-26 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 23, 2000\n| [[Calgary, Alberta]], Canada\n| ..., 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Samer Jaber is stabbed to death at [[Lester B. Pearson High School (Calgary)|Lester B. Pearson High School]] in Calgary by a 16-year-old student. The 16-year-old was later convicted of second-degree murder and sentenced to four years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2000/11/22/calgary_stab001122.html |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120730143438/http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2000/11/22/calgary_stab001122.html |archive-date=2012-07-30 |title=Hundred mourn teenager in Calgary |publisher=Cbc.ca |date=2000-11-23 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/story/2001/04/26/jaberca260401.html |title=Teen gets 4 years for Jaber death |publisher=Cbc.ca |date=2001-04-26 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 18, 2001\n| [[Bromma borough|Bromma]], [[Stockholm]], Sweden\n| ..., 17\n..., 19\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 16-year-old student was shot to death in a toilet facility of the [[Bromma borough|Bromma]] [[Gymnasium (school)|Gymnasium]], in [[Stockholm]], Sweden. Two other students, ages 17 and 19, were charged with the murder.<ref name=\"apsweden118\">{{cite news|first=Stephhan|last=Nasstrom|title=Teen-Ager Shot to Death in Sweden|date=2001-01-18|url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-39966865.html|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20121106054737/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-39966865.html|url-status =dead|archive-date =2012-11-06|agency =[[Associated Press]]|accessdate = 2009-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 5, 2001\n| [[Santee, California]], United States\n| [[Charles Andrew Williams]], 15\n| 2 dead\n| 13 injured\n| Armed with a [[.22|.22-caliber]] [[revolver]], 15-year-old Charles Andrew Williams opened fire in a male toilet facility at [[Santana High School]] in [[Santee, California]], killing one student. Then exiting the restroom, Williams fired indiscriminately at nearby students, killing another student and wounding 13. Shortly afterward he retreated back into the restroom, where he surrendered to police. In June 2002, Williams was sentenced to 50 years in prison.\n|-\n| March 6, 2001\n| [[Limeira]], [[Brazil]]\n| ..., 16\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| During an argument with his girlfriend's brother a 16-year-old student drew a pistol and began shooting at his high school, hitting three students nearby, one of them fatally.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=fqMKAAAAIBAJ&sjid=IU0DAAAAIBAJ&pg=6853,1293079&dq= School shootings raise questions in Brazil], ''The Daily Courier'' (March 11, 2001)</ref>\n|-\n| March 7, 2001\n| [[Williamsport, Pennsylvania]], United States\n| Elizabeth C. Bush, 14\n|\n| 1 injured\n| Elizabeth Bush shoots and injures Kimberly Marchese at Bishop Neumann High School.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1141/is_25_37/ai_73827824/ |title=Girl sentenced in school shooting |publisher=Findarticles.com |date=2001-04-20 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111022005429/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1141/is_25_37/ai_73827824/ |archivedate=2011-10-22 }}</ref>\n|-\n| March 22, 2001\n| [[El Cajon, California]], United States\n| Jason Hoffman, 18\n|\n| 5 injured\n| 18-year-old student Jason Hoffman opened fire with a handgun and shotgun at [[Granite Hills High School (El Cajon, California)|Granite Hills High School]], in [[El Cajon, California]], wounding three students and two teachers. Hoffman committed suicide in prison in 2002.<ref>{{cite news|title=Witnesses Recall School Rampage|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2001/may/11/local/me-62286|newspaper=LA Times|date=May 11, 2001|first=Tony|last=Perry}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Granite Hills gunman's kin file claim vs. county, sheriff|url=http://legacy.utsandiego.com/news/metro/granitehills/20020510-9999_2m10jason.html|newspaper=LA Times|date=May 10, 2002|access-date=June 26, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224122239/http://legacy.utsandiego.com/news/metro/granitehills/20020510-9999_2m10jason.html|archive-date=December 24,