tytv.com/toronto/citynews/news/local/article/73412--teen-dies-after-stabbing-near-oshawa-school |title=Teen Dies After Stabbing Near Oshawa School |publisher=Citytv.com |date=2010-03-30 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629145700/http://www.citytv.com/toronto/citynews/news/local/article/73412--teen-dies-after-stabbing-near-oshawa-school |archivedate=2011-06-29 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/toronto/student-charged-with-murder-in-teens-stabbing-death/article1518884/ |title=Student charged with murder in teen\u2019s stabbing death |publisher=Theglobeandmail.com |accessdate=2011-03-12 |location=Toronto}}</ref> In July 2012, Amakon was convicted of a lesser charge of manslaughter and was sentenced to 6 years of prison.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.durhamregion.com/news-story/3505940-amakon-gets-six-years-for-killing-of-biggie-mcdonald-in-oshawa/ |title=Amakon gets six years for killing of \"Biggie\" McDonald in Oshawa |publisher=[[Durham Region]] |accessdate=September 1, 2013 |location=}}</ref> \n|-\n| April 28, 2010\n| [[Portsmouth, Virginia|Portsmouth]],<br>[[Virginia]],<br>United States\n| Keith Elliott, 15\n|\n| No injuries\n| At around 12:15 pm, a 15-year-old student at [[Woodrow Wilson High School (Portsmouth, Virginia)|Woodrow Wilson High School]] who was suspended earlier in the week for disorderly conduct entered the school through the back door and fired three shots in the cafeteria, with two hitting the ceiling and one entering the wall of a classroom. The suspect left the firearm and fled, but was later apprehended by a security officer and a school administrator. The shooter, 15-year-old Keith Elliott, was charged as an adult with gun violations, armed burglary and assault.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wavy.com/dpp/news/local_news/high-school-suspect-tried-as-adult |title=HS shooting suspect tried as adult |publisher=Wavy.com |date=2010-05-17 |accessdate=2011-