and]], United States\n| Unnamed suspect, 14\n| \n| 1 injured\n| A 16-year-old was seriously injured after being stabbed during a fight at [[Frederick Douglass High School (Prince George's County, Maryland)|Frederick Douglass High School]]. A 14-year-old was arrested.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wjla.com/news/crime/2-students-injured-in-stabbing-at-frederick-douglass-high-in-md--114442|title=Student seriously injured in stabbing at Frederick Douglass High School in Maryland|first=Brad Bell, John Gonzalez, ABC 7|last=News|website=wjla.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|June 2, 2015}}\n| [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]], Canada \n| Unnamed suspect, 17\n| 1 dead\n| \n| A 17-year-old Brett Bourne was stabbed to death in front of [[Kelvin High School]], during a fight. Another 17-year-old was charged with second-degree murder.<ref>[http://www.winnipegsun.com/2015/08/13/kelvin-schoolyard-scuffle-turned-deadly-court-hears Kelvin schoolyard scuffle turned deadly, court hears 9], ''[[Winnipeg Sun]]'', August 13, 2015.</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|June 11, 2015}}\n| [[Bradford]], United Kingdom\n| Student, 14\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 14-year-old boy was charged with attempted murder after a teacher was stabbed in the stomach in a classroom full of pupils.\nBradford crown court heard that the attack was premeditated and partially racially motivated. Uzomah is black and the boy, who is of Pakistani origin, regularly referred to him \"by the epithet beginning with the letter N\"\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/jun/12/bradford-school-stabbing-boy-charged-attempted-murder-teacher|title=Bradford school stabbing: boy charged with attempted murder of teacher |publisher=[[The Guardian]]|website=theguardian.com |date=12 June 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|August 25, 2015}}\n| [[Philippi, West Virginia]], United States\n| Unnamed suspect, 14\n|\n| No injuries\n| At [[Philip Barbour High School]], a 14-year-old male student took his classroom hostage with a .380-caliber handgun, and then surrendered to