q3/| title=Latest on Madison H.S. shooting|work=[[WHIO (AM)]] (Dayton, Ohio)| date=29 February 2016| author1=Rick McCrabb |author2=Lauren Pack |author3=Ed Richter}}</ref> Hancock was apprehended in a nearby wooded field.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.whio.com/news/news/crime-law/accused-madison-hs-shooter-in-court/nqbRN/| title=Parents of Madison H.S. shooting suspect speak; victim returns|work=[[WHIO (AM)]] (Dayton, Ohio)| date=2 March 2016| author=Lauren Clark}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 23, 2016}}\t\n| [[Antigo, Wisconsin]], United States\n| Jacob Wagner, 18\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| Two students at a prom at [[Antigo High School]] were shot and injured by 18-year-old former student Jakob Wagner. Wagner later exchanged fire with a school resource officer in the school's parking lot, and was captured after being shot and wounded by police. He died hours later in a hospital.\n|-\n|{{Dts|October 18, 2016}}\t\n| [[San Francisco, California]], United States\n| \n| \n| 4 injured\n| Four students were shot outside June Jordan High School for Equity, a San Francisco public high school. One female victim was in critical condition, while three male victims suffered minor injuries. Two arrests were made in connection with the shooting. Police stated the shooting appeared to have targeted the female student, with the three other male students hit by gunfire being bystanders  <ref>{{cite web |url = http://abcnews.go.com/US/students-shot-san-francisco-high-school/story?id=42894975/ |title = Students Shot Outside San Francisco High School |publisher= [[ABC News]] }}</ref> Two people were arrested in the shooting.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ww2.kqed.org/news/2016/10/20/three-san-francisco-students-shot-outside-high-school-as-classes-get-out/|title=Update: SFPD Arrests 2 in June Jordan School Shooting|publisher=[[KQED]]|date=October 20, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|November 1, 2016}}\t\n| [[Abbotsford, British Columbia]], Canada\n| Gabriel Klein, 21\n| 1  dead\n| 1 injured\n| A 21-ye